        +section("Turn to a Mobile App")
            span.
              To provide better value, GovContact should be a mobile app. There wouldn't be any link to follow. 
              By taking up visual space inside a phone, the app would also serve as a reminder to a citizen.
              A mobile would also allow a person to call a representative directly from their phone.
        +section("Style Update")
            span.
              After user testing, I decided to update the brand of GovContact.
              Instead of contrasting, polarized colors of red and blue, the primary color is a purple, the unity of the former.
              To convey the feeling of government, I used photographs of building and monuments.
            +img("visual-design.png", "visual design")
        +section("Solution")
            +subheader("2-step Onboarding")
