        +section("Reflection and Next Steps")
          +subheader("Summary")
          span.
            GovContact is an app to connect citizens to their representatives. 
            The process involved research, interviewing users, wireframing, branding, prototyping, and user testing.
            The final solution was a mobile app in which citizens could learn about their representatives and contact them quickly.
          +subheader("Future Steps")
          span.
            The next steps for the app would be to test the click-through prototype with real users.
            The purpose of the usability test is to identify the UX problems that ought to be fixed before development
            Afterwards, and iOS and Anroid app can be programmed and deployed to their respective stores. 
